{"title_page": "Helen Flanagan", "text_new": "{{pp-pc1|small=yes}}\n{{short description|English actress and model}}\n{{Use British English|date=May 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Helen Flanagan\n| caption            = \n| image              = \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1990|8|7|df=y}}\n| birth_place        = [[Bury, Greater Manchester]], England\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| occupation         = {{flatlist|\n* Actress}}\n| television         = ''[[Coronation Street]]'' (2000\u20132012, 2017\u20132018)<br>''[[I'm a Celebrity... Get Me Out of Here!]]'' (2012)\n| partner            = [[Scott Sinclair]] <small>(2009-; engaged)\n| children           = 2\n}}\n'''Helen Joyce Gabriel Flanagan''' (born 7 August 1990)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.itv.com/coronationstreet/characters/rosiewebster/|title=Rosie Webster &ndash; Helen Flanagan|publisher=[[ITV.com]]|accessdate=5 January 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121106123443/http://www.itv.com/coronationstreet/characters/rosiewebster/|archivedate=6 November 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> is an English actress. She is best known for playing the role of [[Rosie Webster]] in the [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] soap opera ''[[Coronation Street]]'' from 2000\u20132012;<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/helen-flanagan-reveals-why-shes-leaving-674693|title=\"I was in a bubble\" - Helen Flanagan says she's looking forward to getting her life back after Corrie|last=Mirror.co.uk|date=2012-02-05|website=mirror|access-date=2019-12-16}}</ref> she reprised the role in 2017, before going on maternity leave on 8 June 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.irishnews.com/magazine/entertainment/2018/04/23/news/helen-flanagan-discusses-hilarious-corrie-exit-storyline-1311795/|title=Helen Flanagan discusses \u2018hilarious' Corrie exit storyline|date=2018-04-23|website=The Irish News|language=en|access-date=2019-12-16}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nFlanagan was born in [[Bury, Greater Manchester]], England.<ref name=\"BBCNews\"/> She attended [[Westholme School]] in [[Blackburn]], [[Lancashire]].<ref name=\"LancashireTelegraph\"/>\n\n==Career==\nFlanagan first appeared as [[Rosie Webster]] in ''[[Coronation Street]]'' in January 2000.<ref name=\"bbc\">{{Cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/entertainment/594408.stm|title=New Rosie Webster for ''Corrie''|date=9 January 2000|accessdate=5 January 2013|publisher=[[BBC News Online]]}}</ref> In 2006, she was nominated for the award of \"Best Dramatic Performance from a Young Actor or Actress\" at the [[The British Soap Awards|British Soap Awards]], losing to [[Ellis Hollins]] of ''[[Hollyoaks]]''.<ref name=\"Channel 5\">{{cite web|url=http://www.channel5.com/shows/celebrity-super-spa/the-celebrities/helen-flanagan|title=''Celebrity Super Spa'' Profile|year=2013|publisher=[[Channel 5 (UK)|Channel 5]] Broadcasting|accessdate=14 October 2013}}</ref> In 2007, she was nominated for \"Villain of the Year\" at the same awards, this time losing to ''Coronation Street'' co-star [[Jack P. Shepherd]].<ref name=\"Channel 5\"/> In 2010, Flanagan appeared in ''Coronation Street'' spin-off ''Coronation Street: A Knights Tale'' as her character Rosie Webster. In 2011, she had her own ''Coronation Street'' spin-off ''Just Rosie'', which explored her character Rosie Webster trying to build a modelling career in London. Flanagan left ''Coronation Street'' in February 2012 to pursue other interests.\n\nIn November 2012, Flanagan participated in the [[I'm a Celebrity...Get Me Out of Here! (UK series 12)|twelfth series]] of ''[[I'm a Celebrity...Get Me Out of Here! (UK TV series)|I'm a Celebrity...Get Me Out of Here!]]'',<ref name=\"LancashireTelegraph\"/> finishing in seventh place.<ref name=\"Channel 5\"/><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/ten/news/television/2013/0526/452729-flanagan-to-pursue-more-reality-roles/|title=Flanagan to Pursue More Reality Offers|date=26 May 2013|publisher=[[Raidi\u00f3 Teilif\u00eds \u00c9ireann|RT\u00c9]] Commercial Enterprises|accessdate=14 October 2013}}</ref> In September 2013 she appeared in ''[[Celebrity Super Spa]]'', a reality-television programme based in a Liverpool Salon on [[Channel 5 (UK)|Channel 5]]. In January 2014, Flanagan starred in an episode of ''[[Celebrity Wedding Planner]]'' alongside [[Hugo Taylor]] on [[Channel 5 (UK)|Channel 5]].<ref name=\"RadioTimes\">{{Cite news|title=Helen Flanagan Becomes a Celebrity Wedding Planner|url=http://www.radiotimes.com/news/2013-03-08/helen-flanagan-becomes-a-celebrity-wedding-planner|last=Cole|first=Tom|date=8 March 2013|work=[[Radio Times]]|publisher=[[Immediate Media Company]]|accessdate=7 October 2013}}</ref> The following August she appeared as agency nurse Kirsty Brompton in an episode of ''[[Holby City]]''.<ref name=\"Digital Spy\">{{cite news|title=Holby City role for ex-Coronation Street star Helen Flanagan|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/soaps/s19/holby-city/news/a568295/holby-city-role-for-ex-coronation-street-star-helen-flanagan.html#~oD6Y545S62kHce|last=Kilkelly|first=Daniel|date=2 May 2014|work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=[[Hearst Magazines]] UK|accessdate=2 May 2014}}</ref> In October 2016, it was announced Flanagan would reprise her role as Rosie in ''Coronation Street'' in February 2017.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.itv.com/news/granada/2016-10-05/helen-flanagan-returns-to-coronation-street-as-rosie-webster/|title=Helen Flanagan returns to Coronation Street as Rosie Webster|work=ITV News|date=5 October 2016|accessdate=21 October 2016}}</ref> She left on maternity leave in June 2018.\n\n==Personal life==\nFlanagan's parents are [[Roman Catholic]]; she has expressed that she still feels a connection to her religious roots.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailystar.co.uk/news/latest-news/twit-wisdom-helen-flanagan-18574203|title=Twit and wisdom of Helen Flanagan|last=reporter|first=Daily Star|date=2012-11-28|website=Dailystar.co.uk|access-date=2019-11-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.her.ie/celeb/im-a-celebrity-star-helen-flanagan-announces-her-most-unlikely-career-move-yet-26773|title=I'm A Celebrity Star Helen Flanagan Announces Her Most Unlikely Career Move Yet!|website=Her.ie|language=en|access-date=2019-11-05}}</ref>\n\nFlanagan became engaged to [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] winger [[Scott Sinclair]] on 31 May 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ok.co.uk/lifestyle/helen-flanagan-engaged-scott-sinclair-14395719|title=Helen Flanagan engagement: All the wedding details as Scott Sinclair proposes|last=Tutton|first=Charlotte|date=2018-06-01|website=OK! Magazine|access-date=2019-12-16}}</ref> They have two daughters.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ok.co.uk/lifestyle/mum-and-baby/helen-flanagan-pregnant-second-baby-14389833|title=Helen Flanagan birth and baby details: Coronation Street star welcomes baby daughter|last=Donaldson|first=Laura|date=2018-06-24|website=OK! Magazine|access-date=2019-11-03}}</ref> \n\nIn June 2013, Flanagan and Sinclair's house in [[Prestbury, Cheshire|Prestbury]], [[Cheshire]] was burgled.<ref name=\"LancashireTelegraph\"/> Flanagan was at home on the night of the incident; the thieves escaped with a mobile phone and items of jewellery.<ref name=\"LancashireTelegraph\"/> She was reported by her spokesman to be \"naturally very shaken\" but \"unharmed\".<ref name=\"LancashireTelegraph\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.lancashiretelegraph.co.uk/news/10491918.Burglars_raid_home_of_former_Coronation_Street_star_Helen_Flanagan/|title=Burglars raid home of former ''Coronation Street'' star Helen Flanagan|date=18 June 2013|newspaper=[[Lancashire Telegraph]]|publisher=[[Newsquest]]|location=[[Blackburn]]|accessdate=31 August 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|2000\u20132012, 2017\u20132018\n|''[[Coronation Street]]''\n|[[Rosie Webster]]\n|\n|-\n|2004\n|''[[Children in Need 