. |last2=Leatherwood |first2=S. |last3=Webber |first3=M.A. |publisher=Marine Species Identification Portal |accessdate=29 August 2015|ref={{harvid|Jefferson et al.}}}}\n*{{cite web |url=http://species-identification.org/species.php?species_group=marine_mammals&id=21&menuentry=groepen |title=Narwhal and White Whale (Family Monodontidae) |last1=Jefferson |first1=T.A. |last2=Leatherwood |first2=S. |last3=Webber |first3=M.A. |publisher=Marine Species Identification Portal |accessdate=29 August 2015|ref={{harvid|Jefferson|2015a}}}}\n*{{cite web |url=http://species-identification.org/species.php?species_group=marine_mammals&id=23&menuentry=groepen |title=Sperm Whale (Family Physeteridae) |last1=Jefferson |first1=T.A. |last2=Leatherwood |first2=S. |last3=Webber |first3=M.A. |publisher=Marine Species Identification Portal |accessdate=29 August 2015|ref={{harvid|Jefferson|2015b}}}}\n*{{cite web |url=http://species-identification.org/species.php?species_group=marine_mammals&id=26&menuentry=groepen |title=Beaked Whales (Family Ziphiidae) |last1=Jefferson |first1=T.A. |last2=Leatherwood |first2=S. |last3=Webber |first3=M.A. |publisher=Marine Species Identification Portal |accessdate=29 August 2015|ref={{harvid|Jefferson|2015c}}}}\n*{{cite web |url=https://www.pbs.org/wnet/nature/ocean-giants-going-aquatic-cetacean-evolution/7577/ |title=Going Aquatic: Cetacean Evolution |publisher=PBS Nature|date=21 March 2012|accessdate=29 August 2015|ref={{harvid|PBS|2012}}}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.interglot.com/dictionary/es/en/search?q=ballena%20asesina|title=Ballena asesina|author=Interglot translation dictionary|work=interglot.com|accessdate=15 January 2016|ref={{harvid|Interglot}}}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.ucmp.berkeley.edu/mammal/cetacea/cetacean.html |title=Introduction to Cetacea: Archaeocetes: The Oldest Whales |publisher=University of Berkeley |accessdate=25 July 2015|ref={{harvid|Berkeley}}}}\n*{{cite web | url=http://www.nmfs.noaa.gov/pr/species/mammals/cetaceans/spermwhale.htm |title=Sperm Whales brain size| publisher=NOAA Fisheries \u2013 Office of Protected Resources |accessdate=9 August 2015|ref={{harvid|NOAAa}}}}\n*{{cite web |url=http://www.defenders.org/whales/basic-facts |title=Mysticetes hunt in groups |publisher=Defenders of Wildlife |access-date=July 24, 2015|ref={{harvid|Defenders of Wildlife}}|date=2012-04-10 }}\n*{{cite magazine |last1=Marrero |first1=Meghan E. |last2=Thornton |first2=Stuart |title=Big Fish: A Brief History of Whaling |url=http://education.nationalgeographic.com/news/big-fish-history-whaling/ |magazine=National Geographic |date=1 November 2011 |accessdate=2 September 2015|ref={{harvid|Marrero|2011}}}}\n*{{cite web |url=http://www.whalingmuseum.org/learn/research-topics/overview-of-north-american-whaling/whales-hunting |title=Whale products |publisher=New Bedford Whaling Museum |accessdate=29 August 2015|ref={{harvid|New Bedford}}}}\n*{{cite web|last1=Stonehouse|first1=Bernard|title=British Arctic whaling: an overview|url=http://www.hull.ac.uk/baw/overview/overview.htm|publisher=University of Hull|accessdate=4 September 2015|date=5 October 2007|ref={{harvid|Stonehouse|2007}}}}\n*{{cite web |url=https://www.pbs.org/wgbh/americanexperience/features/timeline/timeline-whaling/ |title=Timeline: The History of Whaling in America |publisher=PBS|ref={{harvid|PBSa}}}}\n*{{cite web |url=http://www.ifaw.org/united-states/our-work/whales/which-countries-are-still-whaling |title=Which countries are still whaling |publisher=International Fund for Animal Welfare |accessdate=29 August 2015|ref={{harvid|IFAW}}}}\n*{{cite web |url=https://iwc.int/aboriginal |title=Aboriginal Subsistence whaling |publisher=IWC |accessdate=29 August 2015|ref={{harvid|IWCa}}}}\n*{{cite web |url=http://swfsc.noaa.gov/textblock.aspx?Division=PRD&ParentMenuId=228&id=1408 |title=The Tuna-Dolphin Issue |author=NOAA Fisheries \u2013 Office of Protected Resources|work=noaa.gov |accessdate=29 August 2015|ref={{harvid|NOAAb}}}}\n*{{cite web|url=http